Only from here.

1674
00:53:36,100 --> 00:53:37,760
(The secret room switch is inside)

1675
00:53:37,760 --> 00:53:38,520
Hold on.

1676
00:53:38,760 --> 00:53:39,480
Can you close it?

1677
00:53:41,080 --> 00:53:41,720
No.

1678
00:53:41,740 --> 00:53:44,980
(The secret room door
can't be closed from outside)

1679
00:53:46,940 --> 00:53:48,140
(Checking again)
Counterclockwise.

1680
00:53:49,280 --> 00:53:50,280
Okay.

1681
00:53:50,280 --> 00:53:51,440
This changes everything.

1682
00:53:51,440 --> 00:53:51,920
Right.

1683
00:53:51,920 --> 00:53:53,360
Then who closed it for him?

1684
00:53:54,220 --> 00:53:55,900
(How did the killer
escape the secret room?)

1685
00:54:01,440 --> 00:54:03,080
So now the question is this.

1686
00:54:03,320 --> 00:54:04,240
Like we said earlier,

1687
00:54:04,240 --> 00:54:05,000
we can now

1688
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:06,480
be sure he didn't go that way,

1689
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:06,880
right?

1690
00:54:06,880 --> 00:54:07,440
Right.

1691
00:54:07,440 --> 00:54:08,280
(No sign of escape through the window)

1692
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:09,240
He couldn't leave this way either.

1693
00:54:09,240 --> 00:54:10,420
(The switch only works from inside)

1694
00:54:10,500 --> 00:54:11,680
(Both escape routes are blocked)

1695
00:54:11,680 --> 00:54:12,600
Now we have a new problem.

1696
00:54:12,600 --> 00:54:15,520
How did the killer leave this room?

1697
00:54:18,080 --> 00:54:19,000
The swallow's nest is still there.

1698
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:20,840
It can only be closed from inside.

1699
00:54:23,040 --> 00:54:25,080
The killer never came in.

1700
00:54:25,100 --> 00:54:25,760
(The killer never came in?)

1701
00:54:25,760 --> 00:54:27,280
Then how did he kill him?

1702
00:54:27,520 --> 00:54:29,120
How could he kill him without coming in?

1703
00:54:30,680 --> 00:54:32,780
(He Ha's theory)
Ning came in carrying the dummy.

1704
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:33,520
He threw it down.

1705
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:34,880
His father came in.

1706
00:54:34,880 --> 00:54:36,520
They exchanged a bunch of moves.

1707
00:54:36,520 --> 00:54:37,480
They were locked in a standoff.

1708
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:39,560
Then one of you four

1709
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:40,560
stabbed him from behind.

1710
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:41,640
Right here.

1711
00:54:42,120 --> 00:54:43,200
You can kill without entering?

1712
00:54:49,240 --> 00:54:51,440
So he had to kill Ning.

1713
00:54:51,440 --> 00:54:52,080
Yeah.

1714
00:54:54,080 --> 00:54:54,880
Here.

1715
00:54:55,120 --> 00:54:55,520
Here!

1716
00:54:57,280 --> 00:54:58,280
(Silver sword mark)
There really is a sword mark here.

1717
00:54:58,280 --> 00:54:59,280
It really is a sword mark.

1718
00:55:04,880 --> 00:55:06,960
Nice!

1719
00:55:07,760 --> 00:55:08,520
That's it.

1720
00:55:08,900 --> 00:55:12,060
(Trust the detective)

1721
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:13,760
That makes total sense.

1722
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:15,840
That also explains why they died here.

1723
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:16,320
Exactly.

1724
00:55:16,320 --> 00:55:17,000
So the killer

1725
00:55:17,600 --> 00:55:19,040
even told him

1726
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:20,040
the moves.

1727
00:55:20,040 --> 00:55:21,920
Where to ambush, the whole plan,

1728
00:55:21,920 --> 00:55:22,840
it was all set.

1729
00:55:22,840 --> 00:55:24,120
Because he'd rehearsed it.

1730
00:55:24,120 --> 00:55:25,040
This move goes here,

1731
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:26,680
then here, then here.

1732
00:55:26,680 --> 00:55:28,480
In the end, both of them
had to be at the door.

1733
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:29,920
Then he ran over.

1734
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:31,520
No need to open the door.
No need to go in.

1735
00:55:31,520 --> 00:55:32,520
He killed them here.

1736
00:55:32,520 --> 00:55:34,040
Then he pulled out the sword and left.

1737
00:55:34,040 --> 00:55:35,080
Right. Pulled it out and left.

1738
00:55:35,080 --> 00:55:36,840
Because when I saw them,
they were already lying here.

1739
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:38,280
That means he didn't need to come in.

1740
00:55:38,280 --> 00:55:39,200
So it wasn't a locked room.

1741
00:55:39,200 --> 00:55:40,000
And it had nothing to do
with the window.

1742
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:40,320
Right.

1743
00:55:40,880 --> 00:55:41,200
Okay.

1744
00:55:41,200 --> 00:55:43,720
So now we've confirmed

1745
00:55:43,720 --> 00:55:46,720
the murder method and the sequence.

1746
00:55:46,720 --> 00:55:47,800
I think it's clear now.

1747
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:50,840
What we need to discuss next

1748
00:55:50,840 --> 00:55:52,720
is the 11PM night watch.

1749
00:55:52,720 --> 00:55:54,080
What were each of us doing then?

1750
00:55:54,080 --> 00:55:54,280
Right.

1751
00:55:54,840 --> 00:55:55,520
Let's go.

1752
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:56,320
Okay, let's go.

1753
00:55:56,320 --> 00:55:57,300
(Was Ning Waver tricked and killed,
or was there more to it?)

1754
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:03,660
(Interrogation seat)
This is the interrogation spot, right?

1755
00:56:03,840 --> 00:56:04,400
Come on.

1756
00:56:05,220 --> 00:56:05,940
(A fake-out)

1757
00:56:06,680 --> 00:56:07,600
What do you mean?

1758
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:07,920
Sit.

1759
00:56:08,640 --> 00:56:10,440
(You suspect)
Why interrogate me? I'm innocent.

1760
00:56:10,920 --> 00:56:12,800
There should be
a lamp shining like this.

1761
00:56:13,080 --> 00:56:13,440
Right.

1762
00:56:19,580 --> 00:56:21,700
(Focused questioning, 10-minute limit)

1763
00:56:21,700 --> 00:56:22,750
(Goal: Players start a hearing)

1764
00:56:22,750 --> 00:56:24,840
(Question a chosen suspect
or NPC for 10 minutes)

1765
00:56:24,850 --> 00:56:26,060
(Push the investigation forward)

1766
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:30,000
Little killer.

1767
00:56:30,920 --> 00:56:32,360
I'm really not the killer.

1768
00:56:32,360 --> 00:56:33,600
I wish I were.

1769
00:56:35,080 --> 00:56:35,840
Little killer.

1770
00:56:37,280 --> 00:56:38,360
Show me real proof.

1771
00:56:38,360 --> 00:56:39,640
We're not doing pressure tests today.

1772
00:56:39,640 --> 00:56:40,800
Sit properly.

1773
00:56:41,640 --> 00:56:42,520
I'm so nervous.

1774
00:56:43,440 --> 00:56:43,960
Little killer.

1775
00:56:45,260 --> 00:56:46,540
(Pressure)

1776
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:50,200
Little killer.

1777
00:56:51,720 --> 00:56:52,040
Not me.

1778
00:56:52,840 --> 00:56:54,800
I think the killer

1779
00:56:54,800 --> 00:56:55,840
knew Ning Waver.

1780
00:56:55,840 --> 00:56:56,520
(Yang Glory's theory: The killer
was close to Ning Waver)

1781
00:56:56,520 --> 00:56:57,040
No.

1782
00:56:57,040 --> 00:56:58,520
We all knew him.

1783
00:56:58,520 --> 00:56:59,840
I didn't know them.

1784
00:57:00,360 --> 00:57:02,440
I'm a pretty clean girl.

1785
00:57:02,760 --> 00:57:04,160
Why are you so quick to defend yourself?

1786
00:57:05,260 --> 00:57:07,860
(Is it that obvious?)

1787
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:10,080
Okay. We just brought this box

1788
00:57:10,080 --> 00:57:10,920
back from over there.

1789
00:57:10,920 --> 00:57:12,400
The writing on this box...

1790
00:57:13,240 --> 00:57:14,720
Why did he

1791
00:57:14,880 --> 00:57:15,840
wipe it off?

1792
00:57:15,840 --> 00:57:16,160
Right.

1793
00:57:16,160 --> 00:57:17,000
(Da Men Junzi)

1794
00:57:17,000 --> 00:57:18,360
This has to be a clue.

1795
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:21,520
So I was just thinking.

1796
00:57:22,120 --> 00:57:23,680
Second Brother is called Junzi.

1797
00:57:23,680 --> 00:57:24,120
What?

1798
00:57:24,120 --> 00:57:25,400
Junzi Ruyu.

1799
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:26,440
Could it be

1800
00:57:27,080 --> 00:57:29,280
(Ning Que)
that Ning wasn't called Ning Que before?

1801
00:57:29,280 --> 00:57:30,280
No, Ning...

1802
00:57:30,690 --> 00:57:32,320
(What did I just hear?)
Ning Que Wu Lan.

1803
00:57:32,320 --> 00:57:34,440
(A past life story)
I'm Ning Que Wu Lan.

1804
00:57:34,440 --> 00:57:36,040
(Can't hold it in)

1805
00:57:36,040 --> 00:57:37,320
Ning Waver.

1806
00:57:37,340 --> 00:57:38,400
(He Ha's theory: Ning is the mysterious
person and the owner of the box)

1807
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:41,920
For example, Ning might've been
called Junzi before too.

1808
00:57:42,700 --> 00:57:44,340
(Junzi Ru Ning)

1809
00:57:45,260 --> 00:57:46,100
(Junzi Waver)

1810
00:57:46,760 --> 00:57:47,280
It's possible.

1811
00:57:47,720 --> 00:57:49,880
So we can ask

1812
00:57:49,880 --> 00:57:51,840
this rumored Junzi Ruyu.

1813
00:57:52,760 --> 00:57:53,440
Come on, sit.

1814
00:57:53,440 --> 00:57:54,200
Please sit.

1815
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:55,160
Here's your throne.

1816
00:57:56,440 --> 00:57:57,920
Over on your side,

1817
00:57:57,920 --> 00:57:59,360
is there some Jun generation
or something?

1818
00:57:59,640 --> 00:58:00,440
What Jun generation?

1819
00:58:01,040 --> 00:58:01,480
Is...

1820
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:02,520
Is this box yours?

1821
00:58:05,100 --> 00:58:06,540
(Does the box have something
to do with Junzi Ruyu?)

1822
00:58:06,540 --> 00:58:07,340
(Shi Da Men Junzi Ruyu)

1823
00:58:07,720 --> 00:58:08,320
What box?

1824
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:12,520
Sit first.

1825
00:58:18,580 --> 00:58:19,980
("Ding" tense)

1826
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,120
Do you have anything on you?

1827
00:58:23,160 --> 00:58:23,680
What's wrong?

1828
00:58:24,560 --> 00:58:25,360
How about this?

1829
00:58:25,360 --> 00:58:26,120
Search him.

1830
00:58:26,120 --> 00:58:27,520
Let's search him first.

1831
00:58:27,520 --> 00:58:28,720
Got anything? Take it out yourself.

1832
00:58:28,720 --> 00:58:29,640
He does.

1833
00:58:29,640 --> 00:58:30,520
He definitely does.

1834
00:58:30,520 --> 00:58:31,040
Take it out.

1835
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:32,120
Where is it? Hurry.

1836
00:58:32,120 --> 00:58:33,000
What's on his chest?

1837
00:58:33,880 --> 00:58:34,520
Hold on.

1838
00:58:35,160 --> 00:58:36,680
Don't be so rough.

1839
00:58:37,440 --> 00:58:39,200
This isn't rough enough.

1840
00:58:40,840 --> 00:58:41,640
My chest.

1841
00:58:41,640 --> 00:58:42,880
I have a heart here.

1842
00:58:42,880 --> 00:58:43,440
There's a heart mark.

1843
00:58:45,160 --> 00:58:45,520
What's this?

1844
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:46,160
There really is one.

1845
00:58:48,240 --> 00:58:48,640
My lord.

1846
00:58:50,680 --> 00:58:52,000
This again.

1847
00:58:52,000 --> 00:58:53,340
(Missed another chance to show off)

1848
00:58:53,920 --> 00:58:54,560
What does that mean?

1849
00:58:55,120 --> 00:58:56,600
You went over my head.

1850
00:58:56,600 --> 00:58:58,520
With your accomplice too.

1851
00:59:00,080 --> 00:59:00,760
What?

1852
00:59:01,160 --> 00:59:03,320
I missed you in Ginkgo Valley.

1853
00:59:03,320 --> 00:59:05,220
(I missed you in Ginkgo Valley)

1854
00:59:05,440 --> 00:59:06,960
Ginkgo Valley is...

1855
00:59:10,120 --> 00:59:11,880
You already found one, right?

1856
00:59:12,080 --> 00:59:13,120
One isn't enough.

1857
00:59:13,120 --> 00:59:14,280
What else do you want?

1858
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:16,080
Let me do it myself.

1859
00:59:16,360 --> 00:59:17,520
He's got more!

1860
00:59:17,520 --> 00:59:18,760
(Nothing escapes my sharp eyes)
I knew it.

1861
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:20,840
Look.

1862
00:59:20,840 --> 00:59:21,280
Let me see.

1863
00:59:21,760 --> 00:59:22,600
Here, my lord.

1864
00:59:23,780 --> 00:59:25,100
(They don't respect me at all)

1865
00:59:25,360 --> 00:59:26,240
No one's listening to him.

1866
00:59:28,080 --> 00:59:29,400
They were beside me.

1867
00:59:29,400 --> 00:59:30,920
You went over my head.

1868
00:59:30,920 --> 00:59:33,020
(An even worse offense)

1869
00:59:33,040 --> 00:59:33,360
My lord!

1870
00:59:33,360 --> 00:59:36,240
(Detective, please forgive me)
The killer's intent is clear.

1871
00:59:36,400 --> 00:59:39,360
That little killer is up to no good.

1872
00:59:39,960 --> 00:59:42,960
(Detective, I won't do it again)
My lord, I'm innocent!

1873
00:59:44,480 --> 00:59:45,360
There's a letter here.

1874
00:59:48,440 --> 00:59:49,080
Master,

1875
00:59:49,560 --> 00:59:50,360
I'm a useless disciple.

1876
00:59:50,840 --> 00:59:53,240
I even have to sneak over
to drink with you.

1877
00:59:54,040 --> 00:59:55,800
I know you miss me.

1878
00:59:55,800 --> 00:59:57,840
I'll come see you tomorrow.

1879
00:59:58,140 --> 01:00:00,100
(I'll come see you tomorrow)

1880
01:00:00,120 --> 01:00:02,840
Back then, you tricked me
into taking the Qide Sword

1881
01:00:02,840 --> 01:00:04,080
and leaving Tui City.

1882
01:00:04,400 --> 01:00:05,550
I trained for a month.

1883
01:00:06,240 --> 01:00:07,680
When I came back, you were dead.

1884
01:00:08,320 --> 01:00:09,160
My junior was gone.

1885
01:00:09,680 --> 01:00:10,760
Our sect was destroyed.

1886
01:00:12,310 --> 01:00:13,970
I had just hidden the sword

1887
01:00:13,970 --> 01:00:17,940
when Lord Tui dragged me
to Chivalry Manor.

1888
01:00:17,940 --> 01:00:19,790
I thought I might as well fight.

1889
01:00:19,790 --> 01:00:23,300
My last home was gone anyway.

1890
01:00:23,300 --> 01:00:25,540
If I killed a few, I'd come out ahead.

1891
01:00:25,910 --> 01:00:30,640
But your face popped
into my head right away.

1892
01:00:30,640 --> 01:00:32,070
And you started nagging again.

1893
01:00:32,070 --> 01:00:34,720
A hero stands first for the world.

1894
01:00:34,720 --> 01:00:36,770
A hero speaks for the people.

1895
01:00:38,640 --> 01:00:40,560
My master always taught me.

1896
01:00:40,560 --> 01:00:42,760
A hero stands first for the world.

1897
01:00:42,760 --> 01:00:44,560
A hero speaks for the people.

1898
01:00:44,560 --> 01:00:48,900
A hero stands first for the world.
A hero speaks for the people.

1899
01:00:50,000 --> 01:00:50,920
My master.

1900
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:51,400
My disciple,

1901
01:00:52,240 --> 01:00:53,120
your

1902
01:00:53,120 --> 01:00:55,250
path as a hero is yours to find.

1903
01:00:55,820 --> 01:00:57,820
(What is the letter writer's
relationship with Ding Pillar?)

1904
01:00:58,080 --> 01:00:59,400
Master, you're seriously annoying.

1905
01:00:59,830 --> 01:01:01,640
I was already ready to die.

1906
01:01:01,640 --> 01:01:03,240
And you were still talking
about some heroic path.

1907
01:01:04,160 --> 01:01:05,120
But in that moment,

1908
01:01:05,120 --> 01:01:07,120
I really found it.

1909
01:01:07,120 --> 01:01:08,200
Dying is easy.

1910
01:01:08,200 --> 01:01:10,280
But I need to live and do more.

1911
01:01:11,080 --> 01:01:12,440
So I knelt.

1912
01:01:13,400 --> 01:01:16,480
I knelt before everyone at the manor.

1913
01:01:16,480 --> 01:01:17,520
And called him my godfather.

1914
01:01:21,720 --> 01:01:22,920
After Master died,

1915
01:01:22,920 --> 01:01:24,440
I went back to Tui City to find you all.

1916
01:01:24,440 --> 01:01:26,760
I saw Lord Tui take you
to Chivalry Manor.

1917
01:01:26,760 --> 01:01:28,200
I watched from outside the wall.

1918
01:01:28,200 --> 01:01:29,240
I wanted to find a chance to save you.

1919
01:01:29,880 --> 01:01:30,880
But then,

1920
01:01:30,880 --> 01:01:32,160
you called him Father.

1921
01:01:32,160 --> 01:01:33,760
You made Lord Tui your godfather.

1922
01:01:33,760 --> 01:01:35,840
But I need to live and do more.

1923
01:01:36,640 --> 01:01:38,160
So I knelt.

1924
01:01:38,160 --> 01:01:41,220
(Sorting out Ning Waver's identity)
I knelt before everyone at the manor.

1925
01:01:41,220 --> 01:01:42,280
(The truth: He knelt to save his sect)
And called him godfather.

1926
01:01:43,480 --> 01:01:44,320
His own story.

1927
01:01:44,320 --> 01:01:44,800
I think...

1928
01:01:44,800 --> 01:01:45,960
(Ning's final letter)

1929
01:01:45,960 --> 01:01:47,440
From then on,

1930
01:01:47,440 --> 01:01:48,880
that crook pushed me around.

1931
01:01:48,880 --> 01:01:49,960
My fellow disciples hated me.

1932
01:01:50,180 --> 01:01:51,180
Lapdog!

1933
01:01:51,760 --> 01:01:53,640
- Heroes spat on me.
- Ning the Lapdog!

1934
01:01:53,640 --> 01:01:54,720
The people cursed me.

1935
01:01:54,720 --> 01:01:55,480
You sneaky punk!

1936
01:01:55,480 --> 01:01:55,960
It's fine.

1937
01:01:55,960 --> 01:01:57,200
- Let others judge me.
- You're such an ingrate!

1938
01:01:57,200 --> 01:01:57,880
I know right from wrong.

1939
01:01:57,880 --> 01:01:58,880
(Shuai X. Sha Ning. Sha Who. Bao Jiu)
You're an ingrate!

1940
01:01:58,880 --> 01:02:02,080
My path is to light a lamp
in the darkest place.

1941
01:02:02,600 --> 01:02:05,170
So Tui City's night won't last so long.

1942
01:02:05,170 --> 01:02:07,490
I'm willing to live on my knees.

1943
01:02:07,490 --> 01:02:08,460
Later, I realized

1944
01:02:08,460 --> 01:02:11,830
you really can do a lot while kneeling.

1945
01:02:11,830 --> 01:02:14,030
